The paper deals with semi-supervised learning, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of graph-based methods and optimization objectives also suggests that it could be relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks, which could place it under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
